I commuted to my office to take care of new comer. I was supposed not to be busy but in the morning, CSAM set the meeting about how to conduct the meeting with a key person in the client company. I had a scoping meeging with the key person but the manager was not satisfied with the result I delivered. I believe my workshop was as good as it's going to get but there was a room for improvement. I know practice makes perfect.

In the eveneng, I had a drinking session with my new team members. I was not to end up all talk and had a whale of a time at Haneueo, which is one of the best Izakaya in Shigawa. We had a lot of fun and heated discussions about our work. I realized I have to avoid banging my head against the wall and try to feel the way out to make the most out of the situation.

